IRS990.Desc: ASCENSION HOMES, INC. OPERATES HOUSING AND RELATED FACILITIES FOR SENIOR CITIZENS. THE ENTITY WAS FINANCED THROUGH THE U.S. DEPARTMENT OF HOUSING AND URBAN DEVELOPMENT ("HUD") UNDER SECTION 202 OF THE NATIONAL HOUSING ACT AND OPERATES THREE GROUP HOMES CONSISTING OF 20 UNITS. THE ENTITY IS REGULATED BY HUD AS TO RENT CHARGES AND OPERATING METHODS.

Form990ScheduleAPartVIGrp.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: SCHEDULE A, PART III, LINE 12, EXPLANATION OF OTHER INCOME:

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: TENANT SECURITY DEPOSITS HELD IN ACCORDANCE WITH FEDERAL AND STATE REQUIREMENTS.

THE ENTITY RECOGNIZES THE EFFECT OF INCOME TAX POSITIONS ONLY IF THOSE POSITIONS ARE MORE LIKELY THAN NOT TO BE SUSTAINED. MANAGEMENT HAS DETERMINED THAT THE ENTITY HAD NO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT WOULD REQUIRE FINANCIAL STATEMENT RECOGNITION OR DISCLOSURE. THE ENTITY IS NO LONGER SUBJECT TO EXAMINATIONS BY THE APPLICABLE TAXING JURISDICTIONS FOR PERIODS PRIOR TO APRIL 30, 2019.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 3
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ENTITY IS MANAGED BY PEOPLE ENCOURAGING PEOPLE ("PEP"), PURSUANT TO A MANAGEMENT AGREEMENT APPROVED BY HUD. FOR THE YEARS ENDED APRIL 30, 2022, MANAGEMENT FEES CHARGED WERE $8,856. NONE OF THE ORGANIZATION'S OFFICERS OR DIRECTORS LISTED ON FORM 990, PART VII WERE COMPENSATED BY THE MANAGEMENT COMPANY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: GOVANS ECUMENICAL DEVELOPMENT CORPORATION ("GEDCO") IS THE SOLE MEMBER OF THE ENTITY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: GEDCO HAS THE POWER TO APPOINT AT LEAST THREE (3) DIRECTORS TO THE BOARD OF THE ENTITY, WHICH INCLUDE THE PRESIDENT OF GEDCO AND VICE PRESIDENT OF PROPERTIES AT GEDCO.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 8B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ENTITY HAD NO COMMITTEES WITH THE AUTHORITY TO ACT ON BEHALF OF THE GOVERNING BODY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS PREPARED BY AN OUTSIDE ACCOUNTING FIRM. ONCE THE FORM 990 IS PREPARED, IT IS REVIEWED BY THE CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER OF THE ENTITY'S SOLE MEMBER, GOVANS ECUMENICAL DEVELOPMENT CORPORATION. A COMPLETE COPY OF THE FORM 990 IS PROVIDED TO ALL BOARD MEMBERS PRIOR TO THE RETURN BEING FILED WITH THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ANY DIRECTOR, OFFICER, KEY EMPLOYEE, OR COMMITTEE MEMBER HAVING AN INTEREST IN A CONTRACT OR OTHER TRANSACTION PRESENTED TO THE BOARD OR A COMMITTEE THEREOF FOR CONSIDERATION, AUTHORIZATION, APPROVAL, OR RATIFICATION SHALL MAKE A PROMPT, FULL, AND FRANK DISCLOSURE OF HIS INTEREST TO THE BOARD OR COMMITTEE PRIOR TO ACTING ON SUCH CONTRACT OR TRANSACTION. IF A CONFLICT IS DEEMED TO EXIST, SUCH PERSON SHALL NOT VOTE ON, NOR USE HIS OR HER PERSONAL INFLUENCE ON, NOR PARTICIPATE (OTHER THAN TO PRESENT FACTUAL INFORMATION OR TO RESPOND TO QUESTIONS) IN THE DISCUSSIONS OR DELIBERATIONS WITH RESPECT TO, SUCH CONTRACT OR TRANSACTION. SUCH PERSON MAY BE COUNTED IN DETERMINING THE EXISTENCE OF A QUORUM AT ANY MEETING WHERE THE CONTRACT OR TRANSACTION IS UNDER DISCUSSION OR IS BEING VOTED UPON. THE MINUTES OF THE MEETING SHALL REFLECT THE DISCLOSURE MADE, THE VOTE THEREON, AND, WHERE APPLICABLE, THE ABSTENTION FROM VOTING AND PARTICIPATION, AND THAT A QUORUM WAS PRESENT. THE BOARD MAY ADOPT CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICIES REQUIRING REGULAR ANNUAL STATEMENTS FROM DIRECTORS, OFFICERS AND KEY EMPLOYEES THAT DISCLOSE EXISTING AND POTENTIAL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST; AND CORRECTIVE AND DISCIPLINARY ACTIONS WITH RESPECT TO TRANSGRESSIONS OF SUCH POLICIES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ENTITY MAKES ITS FORM 990 AVAILABLE FOR PUBLIC INSPECTION AS REQUIRED UNDER SECTION 6104 OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. THE RETURN IS AVAILABLE ON GUIDESTAR.ORG AND OTHER SIMILAR TYPES OF WEBSITES. IN ADDITION, THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS, AND GOVERNING DOCUMENTS ARE AVAILABLE UPON WRITTEN REQUEST.
